included.description: Spearheaded exploratory research into what Millennials like and dislike about Hollywood. Analyzing generational data and movies that tested well with Millennials, this white paper concluded that Millennials prefer films that connect to them on some social or emotional level. The movie Ted, which was released around the time of this paperâs development, proved to be a great example of a movie with high reliability and success.

included.description: Conducted observational research on Twitter to study communication patterns between fans and brand handles. The hypothesis was that followers prefer to interact with companies consistent with dyadic relationships: where both parties are engaged in the conversation. The results were inconclusive in terms of engagement preferences, but revealed that followers RT links to videos, articles, and pictures far more than other media.
included.title: Links, Videos, or Retweets?: Measuring Engagement on Twitter
